Description: Lid of a miniature canopic jar (model) in the form of a falcon's head with incised details of eyes, beak and hair, in glazed composition; representation of Qebehsenuef, one of the four son of Osiris; traces of blue turquoise glaze.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (FA.16)
Condition: Rather fair, though fragmentary and chipped
